text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
“how dare he touch me like that..” we conducted an interview with @eboniemarie__ an african-american #melaninrichgal who was brave enough to share her story about being sexually assaulted. “i’d like to share my story about how black women are the most disrespected people group and how we’re looked down upon,” she told us.
✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨
april 18, 2015.... the first time in my life that i felt degraded as a black woman. how dare he touch me like that? why me? is it the sight of my curves or the innocence in my eyes? 
the pain i felt was like no other and i asked god when would this suffering be over. it was that day when i felt that, as a black woman, we are seen as an easy target and naive. 
the recovery process for me was extremely hard and triggering. i went through a dark moment and i never felt so alone in my life. i was shamed and bashed for speaking up. i was called a liar by those who were close to me. i didn’t expect to lose so many people in my life because i spoke up for myself. there were days that i did not want to get out of bed and go to school because of the image people had of me at that moment. this really tested how strong i was as a black woman and it took a lot for me to have genuine forgiveness towards those who turned their backs on me. but wait... how do you forgive someone who physically took advantage of you and made you feel less than what you’re worth? it doesn’t happen over night or within a month. you have to decide if you want that to define your worth. i forgave, but i didn’t forget. i had to learn that my blackness doesn’t define who i am as a person and especially as a woman. since my wounds have healed, i’ve decided to share my story. 
in the words of tupac, “and since we all came from a woman
got our name from a woman and our game from a woman
i wonder why we take from our women
why we rape our women, do we hate our women?
i think it's time to kill for our women
time to heal our women, be real to our women....keep ya head up” 
we are extremely thankful to @eboniemarie__ for  being so courageous as to share her story with us. “i’ve been quiet about my experience,” she said “but i think it’s the time to let others know.”
name: Melanin Rich Gallery

the recovery process for me was extremely hard and triggering. i went through a dark moment and i never felt so alone in my life. i was shamed and bashed for speaking up. i was called a liar by those who were close to me. i didn’t expect to lose so many people in my life because i spoke up for myself. there were days that i did not want to get out of bed and go to school because of the image people had of me at that moment. this really tested how strong i was as a black woman and it took a lot for me to have genuine forgiveness towards those who turned their backs on me. but wait... how do you forgive someone who physically took advantage of you and made you feel less than what you’re woh? it doesn’t happen over night or within a month. you have to decide if you want that to define your woh. i forgave, but i didn’t forget. i had to learn that my blackness doesn’t define who i am as a person and especially as a woman. since my wounds have healed, i’ve decided to share my story. 
in the words of tupac, “and since we all came from a woman
got our name from a woman and our game from a woman
i wonder why we take from our women
why we rape our women, do we hate our women?
i think it is time to kill for our women
time to heal our women, be real to our women....keep ya head up” 
we are extremely thankful to  for  being so courageous as to share her story with us. “i’ve been quiet about my experience,” she said “but i think it’s the time to let others know.”

text_retweet:
reposted from @earthlove777 -  rp @jessyforthevoiceless why the dairy industry is cruel on every level.👇🏼
• 
when a mother cow gives birth, her calf will be removed within 36 hours, so the farmers can steal and sell the milk that is meant for her baby. (organic-, free range-, pasture raised- farm or not.)
• 
cows are pregnant for 9 months, like humans, and there's a natural, strong bond between a mother cow and her calf.
so following their traumatic separation, the mother will bellow and scream for days, wondering where her baby is. 
the answer depends on the gender of the calf. if male, he will probably either be shot and tossed into a bin, or he'll be sold to be raised for veal, which delays his death by just a matter of months. • 
calves who are sold for veal will be stuck inside a small pen or a veal crate so they won't develop any muscle tissue so their 'meat' stays tender.
they stay there until they are transported for slaughter at only 18 - 20 weeks old.
• 
if the calf is female, she will usually be prepared for her own entry into dairy production, where she will face the same cycle of terror that her mother is trapped in: forced impregnation, the theft of her babies and the endless milking. • 
once the dairy cows are so worn out that they have produced all the milk they can, they are sent to slaughter, usually at around five years of age; the average natural lifespan of a cow is 18 - 22 years. 
their meat often ends up in low-grade burgers or pet foods.
• 
help bring an end to an industry that is violent, unnatural and heart breaking on every level 🙏.
---------------------------------------------------------------

text:
i love this photo taken by a friend. the moments of having the space to be me is good for my soul. 
women in their prime is not looked at in the same way as men in their prime.  im 34 and i can stretch and kick and do the splits cause i’m 34 and a bad ass.  but when a mentor told me at 33 i’m not a spring chicken any more i was like wtf does that really mean.? yeah i know being 26 was amazing but i wouldn’t do it over again.  i love traveling and doing life differently.
i choose to not have kids yet and still may not.  im an auntie though and i’ve got a lot of kid energy so i’m okay with that. 
my choices have changed and so has life!! 3 years ago before the #metoomovement and being apart of the so called statistic of assault of an assault.  let’s say a lot of mixed emotions.  the fear of being apart of a statistic is upsetting and unnerving but as a movement started as others stood in the light battling from darkness... someone said it gets easier. 
i honestly haven’t had the same relationship with my body as i did.  my body doesn’t feel as sexy.. it doesn’t feel great being a woman sometimes.  sometimes i love it but sometimes i hate it.  last year i had a pdsd moment when seeing someone who resembled the perpetrator.  the experience is real everyone!! whoever hasn’t truly experienced or knows what pdsd is just shut your mouth and open your hearts.  my body of flight or fight, heart palpitation and complete anger and fear.  this comes with different kinds of emotions and regrets followed by wisdom and love for ones self. 
right now i’m working on things that i love and it’s all worth the struggle.  my identity is emerging and shaken up.  my feeling of being lost comes and goes and i remember life’s awesome and the struggle is just as important to work through as it is to hug myself.  wtf world. 
being in school again is empowering and gratifying. 
also if you don’t know me i make shit happen, i bring people together and i care maybe too much!!! #metoo #womenempowerment #ambition #ambitiouswomen #ambitious #boss #entrepreneur #change #jesy #jesygart #sharing #vulnerability #strength #growth #artistic #beauty #bossbitch #fem #feminist #feministart

text:
i am my ancestor’s wildest dreams. i think about the black literary queens that have come before me and i can’t help but to honor them. in a time where education and expansion of the mind was only limited to our oppressors, they made a way. those learnings and that eagerness to do and become better is in my blood. 
i believe that my ancestors not only dreamed of what their future lineage would become, but what they themselves could have been or wanted to be had they not been subjected to the inhumane conditions of slavery. i am a walking, living, breathing example.  i’ll continue to pass on our stories of rising and overcoming in honor of you.
_______________________________
toni morrison: the first african american woman to receive the nobel prize for literature. 
phillis wheatley: the first african american woman to become a published poet. 
gwendolyn brooks: the first african american woman to receive a pulitzer prize for poetry. 
angela davis: respectfully, a bad ass. activist and professor. third woman in history to appear on the fbi’s “most wanted list” 
harriet jacobs: an escaped enslaved woman who became an active abolitionist, published incidents in the life of a slave girl in 1861.

marry ann shadd carry: she wrote on abolition and other political issues, including starting a newspaper in ontario urging black americans to flee to canada after the passage of the fugitive slave act. she became a lawyer and a women's rights advocate.

audre lorde
frances harper 
maya angelou 
lucy parsons 
ida b. wells 
mary church terrell
jessie fauset 
#bhm #blackhistorymonth #botm #books #womensmarch #womensempowerment #metoo #blackauthors #girlpower #february #women #selflove #empower

text:
🧡the golden rule of life🧡
.
. 🧡treat yourself the way you treat and want others to feel🧡
.
. 🧡many survivors subconsciously accept, and feel they’re not worthy of being treated with respect,  and love. when you stay in these places and speak this language to yourself, then that’s your unhealed abuse talking.
.
. 😡abuse is a liar!
.
. 🧡you are worthy of love, you are worthy of kindness, you are worthy of healing, you are worthy of respect, you are worthy of happiness, you are worthy of self care.
.
. 🧡be kind to yourself, forgive yourself, heal yourself, and know that you are not your scars, and worthy of self live first.
.
.

text:
women are subject to distinct double-standards in the workplace and there is one bright stage where this stands out more than others: the campaign trail. a record number of women, count them, six! have announced their candidacy for the democratic nomination for 2020.  this is a groundbreaking race, no doubt.  and they’ll be going up against a republican candidate with a long a documented history of sexist remarks and actions, among (ahem) other things. . . .⠀
but as exciting as this progress may be, it’s already starting to feel like groundhog day with talk of the “likability trap”, judgments about appearance and stereotypes that reward stereotypically “masculine” leadership traits in men and punish the exact same behaviors in women. we want women to be strong, but not too strong. and perhaps the most infuriating fact is this: people will not vote for a woman who they deem as fully qualified if they don’t “like” her, but they vote for a man who they see as qualified but they don’t like. . . .⠀
read this article from @nytimes and think of it as a clear preview of this next presidential campaign. on the campaign trail, in workplaces, and in conversations with friends/family/coworkers, it’s up to all of us to recognize and challenge gender bias when we see it. ⠀
. . .⠀
(story and 📸 from @nytimes: ‘a woman, just not that woman’: how sexism plays out on the trail - the new york times https://t.co/nntceqeadi)
. . .
#hruprise #timesup #sexism #campaign #harassment #metoo #metoomovement

text:
today is national clean out your computer day.  lol i never knew this was thing, however, it’s much needed for me.  i keep everything!!! i still have old high school and college papers. i need to upload all my photos to an external hard drive, i have so many pictures. i am the family documentarian, i am the one with all the photos, seriously, i even delete some and i still have too many.  someday, the kids in our family will appreciate it.  anyways, just like i cleaned out my closet last week i need to clean out my computer.  i challenge you to go through your computer and get rid of things you don’t need right now. upload it to an external hard drive.  while i’m being honest here i need to do the same with my phone. 🤦🏻‍♀️
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#holisticliving #wellness #wellnessinsideout #agouldstory #fgnaturalwellness #selfcare #metoo #healthyliving #healthyhome #healthyfamilies #springcleaningearly

text:
text from dana:
i was thinking to myself this morning how god is so gracious to heal our wounded hearts. after years of abuse, pain and hardship i can honestly say that the pain has been washed away through god's love. it is amazing to me that although the memories are still there, the hurt i used to feel when thinking on past events is gone. now i can look back and rejoice in god with thankfulness for carrying me through and bringing restoration to my life.

it really is miraculous if you think about it, how god can do that for us. you see, when the word of god says he will heal the brokenhearted and bind up our wounds, it is so very true. if you feel this day that the pain might never go away because it has been with you so long - be encouraged for god is about to do something new in your life. he will wash away the painful memories and restore your heart to wholeness.

how can this be you may ask. go to the lord and express the pain you are feeling inside, be completely honest like you are talking to your very best friend. there is no shame you will experience while baring your heart to the lord for in his presence there is only perfect love and acceptance.

as you lay everything out before the lord, he will start to guide your thoughts and a transformation will begin to take place in your mind. just letting it all out is where the healing begins. know that you are always in a safe place when you share your heart with the lord. he will never judge you. he thinks the world of you - you are his perfect creation. he loves you just the way you are with all your imperfections.

rest in the arms of jesus this day as you share your heart with him. he will lift those burdens off your heart, mind and soul and help to unravel the painful thoughts and replace them with the sweet touch of his perfect love.

you are loved,
dana

.⠀

.⠀
they’re using you to make money off of you. it’s a scam. you’re not a pawn for them to play with. you don’t have to buy into the bs.

text:
yesterday was the 4th international day of women and girls in science.
even though i am a little bit late now (completely forgot about it tbh) i wanted to write about it. growing up i competed in science fairs. doing botany, some engineering, some geography and each year i was amazed at the amount of girls competing. during the six years i went there were more and more of us (i remember a year where little me was completely amazed at a girl competing with a math project. or another one with something it related.) and it was glorious. 
each year i was asked the same type of question at least once. „how does it feel to do this? as a girl i mean“, most people didn’t focus on my projects but on girls as a person and while the guys usually looked like real scientists in the newspaper there always had to be something whimsical about their female counterparts. it surely got better, but there’s still work to be done.

i partly write this for 12 year old me who was terrified of being „too much of a nerd“ and all the little girls i spoke to over the years, because there’s nothing wrong with that. be a nerd. build that thing. finish that program you started writing. do the research you missed in the books you read. don’t be afraid to become an expert in one field, however stupid it might seem. ask questions. it’s ok to take up that space, it’s yours as much as anybody else’s. 
and as things are getting easier in some areas, it’s important to reflect on one’s own place. for me science and research are open and welcoming fields, mostly because i had people on my side who allowed me to succeed. i had the enormous privilege of being introduced to it at a very early age and just because it was like that for me, doesn’t mean it’s the same for anyone.
help others succeed. it doesn’t matter whether it’s your child, your sister, a friend, a coworker or just someone in the same field. support them. look out for each other, help them have the same opportunities that made you end up where you’re right now.
the world needs more good scientists! 
scroll through the pictures to see awesome scientists, go to beyondcurie.com to learn more about them and their amazing work!
🌈ruth

text:
la de hoy degollada, la del otra día descuartizada, la de mañana... porque no ha sido la última, mañana asesinarán a otra, pasado a otra... ¿y tú cómo te sientes, te escandalizas? tú que te molestas cuando te advierten que tus piropos no gustan, que te vas de putas pero lo más sagrado para ti es una madre, que presumes de lo que jamás hay que presumir porque entre otras cosas evidencian carencias, tú que aprendiste a tocar y no a acariciar porque viste o sigues viendo demasiado porno, tú que quizás veas a la mitad de la población como objetos y no como lo que realmente son, personas, tú que no has matado a nadie y seguramente no lo hagas... tú podriás hacer mucho más de lo que haces, que es nada.

today's slaughtered, the other day dismembered, tomorrow ... because it was not the last, tomorrow they will kill another, passed on to another ... and how do you feel, you scandalized? you who get upset when they warn you that your compliments do not like you, that you're a bitch but the most sacred thing to you is a mother, that you presume of what you never have to show off because, among other things, they show deficiencies, you who learned to play and not to caress because you saw or you still see too much porn, you might see half of the population as objects and not as what they really are, people, you who have not killed anyone and you probably do not ... you can do much more than what you do, which is nothing.

text:
#metoo. not so long ago, the internet was ablaze with the exposure of workplace harassment. around the same time, we asked - what role could management play to ensure women feel safe in garment factories in the "me too" era? especially when this management is predominantly male, and the workers mostly female. does training workers' direct supervisors in soft skills such as effective communication and gender relations, change the work environment? at the end of the day, does it make them "better managers" and make business sense?

special shoutout to @tiki_lava for designing a snapshot of the factory floor for our annual zine, which being true to our aspirational nature, shows a female supervisor at the forefront 🙅🏽‍♀️ 📸: @emulsionpixel

text: in a few minutes, i’ll be interviewed by rachel martin with morning edition @npr. they are getting stories from survivors of sbc clergy sexual abuse. watching this story emerge from the excellent investigation and journalism from both the fw star telegram as well as the recent houston chronicle article has been an honor and i really, really, really hope that the sbc makes the changes it needs to make. it is not just my story i’m telling. i will do my best to honor every story and every survivor that is out there. this is your story too. please pray that i represent the courage and strength each survivor has, and that i do not waver in the pursuit of the reconciliation we are due, as well as the weight that comes with protecting people now and in the future. #sbctoo #churchtoo #metoo #southernbaptist
name: Anne Marie Miller

text:
chá para bebê 🤔
.
o que posso dizer é que valentina começou a ter muitas cólicas e gases, eu não sabia mais o que fazer ... o pediatra receitou colikids, paracetamol e espasmo dimentiliv, mas mesmo assim no sábado dia 02/02/2019 ela estava com muita dor, chorando muito até o momento em que ela ficou roxa de tanto chorar e o som não saia, fiquei apavorada e levei para o hospital, lá me disseram que não podiam fazer nada por que cólicas são normais em bebês e não teria como  atender ela até por que seria um risco para ela ficar esperando atendimento em meio ouros doentes, ela já estava médica pelo pediatra e infelizmente o hospital não faz atendimento para cólicas e eu teria que ir segunda-feira ao posto de saúde... voltei com minha filha chorando muito para casa, chegando em casa minha mãe falou do chá de funcho e foi aí que iniciei a dar o chazinho para ela e desde então ela tem tido pouquíssimas cólicas e logo passa!
.
agora eu dou chá de camomila e funcho para ela, obviamente que não fico oferendo toda hora apenas ofereço quando ela está com cólica; confesso que fiquei triste em dar o chá pois minha intenção era dar exclusivamente o peito até os 6 meses, mas eu não posso deixar minha filha com dor por uma escolha que eu fiz!
.
o que o pediatra falou sobre o chá ? ele disse que não posso dar muito, nao posso forçar ela tomar e não colocar açúcar !
.
.
.
mamadeira @personalpauladurval @paularegina775
.
.

text:
some of us don't like to face what happened to us. we do many things to try and avoid the pain and hurt. we think we have healed when in all honesty, we have not.  we gravitate to people, places, and things(social media; i.e. tinder, fb)that are not good for us, but provides the attention we seek. we are unaware of who we are and what real love is. instead of taking the time to heal, seeing a therapist or counseling, we keep jumping from relationship to relationship.

please seek out help and get free from the abuse and trauma you suffered. trust me, it's very beneficial to becoming your whole self.

#heal #trauma #metoo #help #counselors #therapist #agapelove #godheals #selflove #realrelationships #coach @author #survivor

text:
yesterday i got triggered. i was riding back home from a far away land and ended up encountering some people and scenarios that felt familiar. and not in that good, mmm this tastes just like grandma’s pumpkin pie way. in the way where you shut your eyes and hope that when you open them you’ll find it was all just a nightmare and you’re awake now, safe in your own bed.

so i waited until i was, in fact, home safe in my own bed, and i wept. i wept for my fear, its power, my immobility. i wept for the almosts, the near misses, the close calls. i wept for the constancy of this pain that i thought was an old scab but right then felt like a fresh wound.

but for every bit of pain, we can choose to suffer quietly alone, or share our pain and commune because of it. because we’re human, and we all have to learn: it’s ok to not be ok.

do share your struggle with those around you? does it make you feel lighter or heavier?
.
.
.
.
📸: @drawnbymary

text:
a cold wave hits... the body shudders, suddenly you feel light headed, eyes become heavy and droopy, spirit even
more so…
you don't feel like doing anything: moving, eating, talking, walking, none of it .. and then comes
pain, you feel it in your heart; piercing, an empty void, all the activities that once excited you
now feel like a burden.. it gets difficult to breathe…
some will say sleep it off, some will say shake it off.
but hey, do whatever you want.
you want to scream, do it, you want to cry, do it, you want to do nothing, do nothing.
most importantly stay with the feeling, embrace it, be kind to yourself. and then try to trace it;
what am i feeling in my body? can i put a finger on it? familiarise yourself with it, be
acceptive…
your body needs you, your mind needs you, just like we are told “be there for your friends”. be there for yourself, dear friend.
p.s. seen an ecg machine? it says that you are alive until your life line is going up and down.
depression is one low point or i should say a phase in one’s life which cannot shatter you for
lifetime but teaches worth lessons. be with your feelings and instead of getting anxious about
why are you so dull just let this feeling flow. talk to someone, reach out. don’t hesitate to talk,if
you want to consult a therapist then go for it. don’t have second thoughts on it. we all have our
means of seeking help. it’s okay to talk and it’s okay to feel sad. it’s okay to just roll up yourself
in the bed at times and not wake up until the heart says. till then, take care of yourself.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
all of my finished drawings from february 2018 -2019 together in one place!!! this is definitely going to take up a special place on the wall of my art room!

i have struggled off and on since high school to regain my artistic confidence after losing interest due to a personal experience.  seeing all of the work i put in over the past year come together like this is really something special!  i'm so proud of this!!! i'm going to keep pushing myself as an artist this year, and imagining what my collection of drawings will look like this time in 2020 has got me so pumped!

to all of the artists out there who are struggling with confidence in themselves as artists: you are not alone!  keep going!  you rock! i love you!

text:
we are thrilled to share that 20% of donations of $20 or more will go directly to the american civil liberties union (aclu). please make a donation through our indiegogo campaign: 
https://bit.ly/2gmfj5k

house on fire is a play for today, exposing the ways in which white supremacy twists language and narrative to try to justify its actions. yet the play is also contemporary in how it is made: with a diverse cast and production team (majority poc and female actors), a production devised in collaboration from an open performance text by all on the production team. by utilizing this broad set of voices, in such a democratic manner, we hope to subvert the hive mind mentality and inflammatory rhetoric of trumpian america, and expose it for the babble that it is.

text:
these days the craze for social networking sites is equivalent to oxygen for a human.not only  the so called “millennials” but every age group and every generation is allured by the beauty of social media.social media as they say is both a boon and a curse.a lot of people have literally made their lives out of social media....as they say “one idea can change your world”,youth today has started new startups and have exhibited their scintillating talent!
from comedy to ted talks,social media has swayed into critical issues that need our attention!
social media has helped us to connect to the world,to know the best practices of the other side of our world,it is the basis for all these exchange programmes conducted in schools and colleges.....
on the other side of the coin are the ill effects of this treasure
cyber crime,robbery,eve teasing,depression,loss of confidence,etc are all the by-products of social media!a recent example i have seen is from face book a couple posted a check in of somewhere and some relative of theirs asked in a comment that when would they come back.....they disclosed all the details......when they came back there house was robbed.....what i want to say is people forget that they can’t put everything “out there”!this is social not personal.....people make fake accounts to allure young men and women through these sites,all of which is saddening.
i just want to say where the #metoo movement,an outcome of social media has let a lot of girls to come out of the cocoon to speak it has also made a lot of genuine men suffer!
it is “we” who have to strike the balance between doing it and not over doing it.....you know we should use this amazing feature not misuse it!
thankyou

text:
love is timeless

the clock is ticking
it feels like life is kicking

kicking me down
and sometimes toss me around

im trying to find love or myself
so many times i fall down

like the sticks to a drum
so many ups and downs
yet i dont hear a sound

this normal pace 
is like a fast race

as if we are chasing after a reality
something that we can touch or see

yet time is truly of the essence
are you free or do you feel hell bent

and in all this chaos...the truth is
we simply want someone to love us

so what is love if its not infinite
we can wake up happy and be at peace at night

yet in this reality we chase for
love is something of a far flight
so we quickly shut the door
forgetting that love is on thw inside

so how can you find love
if you always chasing time

it runs out each day yet we still alive
so love has nothing to do with time

love is so powerful that if we all love
only then can we truly come alive

love is limitless.
love is timeless.
love is life

text:
if you are reading this kachru and monica, i hope you guys are together and have the strength to overcome the tournament you've been through. no couple should be treated so alfwul.
-
-
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
viele wissen es ja bereits durch interviews, oder durch meine songs: mir wurde sehr lange (ca. 16 jahre lang) sexuelle/rituelle gewalt angetan. hauptsächlich durch den erzeuger meiner mutter. "großvater" möchte ich nicht mehr sagen, denn er ist kein "großer vater" für mich. ich gehe sehr offen mit meiner vergangenheit um, denn so kann ich es besser verarbeiten. außerdem zeige ich so anderen betroffenen, dass sie darüber sprechen können/sollen/dürfen, denn schweigen macht krank. 
die wahrheit kann heilen...auch wenn es zeit braucht. und die wahrheit kann helfen, um den kreislauf aus tätern und opfern zu durchbrechen. 
letztes jahr, hatte ich eine anhörung bei der "unabhängigen kommission zur aufarbeitung sexuellen kindesmissbrauchs". ich wollte es erst jetzt öffentlich machen, um sicher zu gehen, dass die aufzeichnungen und aufnahmen meiner anhörung auch dort ankommen, wo sie hinsollen. 
da an dem mir begangenen missbrauch mehrere männer beteiligt waren, welche auch im staatsapperat in hochrangigen posten tätig waren/sind, wollte ich einfach kein risiko eingehen.
als ich 2011 die anzeige bei der polizei machte, hätte ich mir schon denken können, dass diese nicht gegen einen ehemaligen polizei-chef ermitteln würden, den sie persönlich kannten.
aber wie unverschämt man mit mir umgehen würde, dass man beweisen nicht nachgehen würde und man zeugenaussagen keinerlei bedeutung geben würde, und ja, dass sogar ein wissenschaftlich falsches gutachten gemacht werden würde....davon hatte ich keine ahnung. es war wie im film und doch es läuft leider wirklich so.
man kann es kaum glauben. es gab nicht einmal eine befragung/ vernehmung des täters, geschweige denn eine anklage.
seitdem habe ich mich aus eigener kraft gewehrt, um den tätern zu zeigen, dass ich keine angst habe und dass ich kein opfer bleibe.
deswegen bin ich nach münchen gefahren und habe bei der kommission ausgesagt. das hat für die täter keinerlei rechtliche konsequenzen, denn es ging hier um präventivarbeit.
ich habe ausgesagt, damit anderen kindern früher geholfen wird und damit sich das traumatherapeutische angebot für betroffene verbessert.
#morgaine #geschichtenerzählen #metoo #aufschrei #überlebt

text:
overthinking is a really good way to stay stuck.  it is a good way to not move forward.  have you thought of an idea that you were excited about?  instead of putting your idea into action, you sat and thought about it?  and then thought about it more?  dissected it?  focused on all that could go wrong?  yet, didn’t acknowledge what could go well? .

it is scary to try something new. it can be terrifying to step out of our comfort zone, but we will not grow as a person unless we try something new.  stop the overthinking!  it is stifling you and preventing you from shining.  it is your time to shine 🌟

text:
what we talk about when we talk about rape 🖋️sohaila abdulali
✒️sohaila abdulali, a writer and rape survivor, who was gang-raped at the age of seventeen, has written this book as a fighter, who decided not to lose but to explore her life. she was the also the first indian rape survivor who speaks out about rape.
🚫
there are many taboos in our country or world and rape is one of them, which is a traumatic experience and must be shared with someone who could help the victim to get them out of this filthy situation of guilt and dishonor.
🚫
author argues that rape isn't clarified yet, which is a global issue. sometimes victim doesn't know what type of sexual harrassment is termed as rape and which one isn't.
🚫
sohaila talked about the celebrities like taylor swift, kalki koechlin, etc. and their traumas of harassment. she talked about marital rape and casting couches which is unacceptable and unreliable to our society.
🚫
author pointed out that being silent about rape is catastrophic, keeping secret about sexual harrassment is not a way out instead opening up will took out the trepidation.
🚫
girls aren't the only one who go through this horrific state, boy could also get sexually abused. ( even,  animals aren't safe. )  author debate about this by giving example of survivors ( old, prostitutes, housewifes, sisters, etc.. ), whom she came across, who had been abused by their close ones since their childhood.
🚫
sohaila said what we are unable to express, she saw and experienced which we can just think in our wildest dreams. she showed us through this book that the only way to revive your honour is to speak up, being silent is like giving power to the accuser to do this with others too.
🚫
after " manto ", this is my second heart-wrenching read. this book helped me and of course it will help you too, to understand the stiffness of a rape victim acutely. this is a must read.
.

text:
not enough is done to protect african women. african women have been taught that it is their duty to protect men even at the expense of their own safety. but who is protecting african women? abuse of many forms are rampant in africa, women are not safe but african women are told to keep quiet. 
the culture of silence must end, silence is a tool of patriarchy and we must resist. a man hits a woman to silence her, rape culture exists to silence victims, to drown out our voices, to question our stories. 
they belittle and dismiss our stories but we must remember to resist. 
the culture of silence must stop, women who have been shrouded in shame will finally share their stories and make their voices heard! 
y'all want a #metooafrica ? it's a revolution and we are going to do this.  reply with an emoji to show your support 😂💜💜

text:
fairfax accuser to speak at event about the #metoo movement
#
vanessa tyson (photo courtesy stanford university) vanessa tyson (photo courtesy stanford university) stanford, calif. – one of the women accusing virginia lt. gov. justin fairfax of sexual assault is scheduled to be part of a panel discussion about the #metoo movement on tuesday. the symposium is called “betrayal and courage in the age of #metoo” and it’s being held at stanford university’s center for advanced study in the behavioral sciences where dr. vanessa tyson works. dr. tyson claims lt. gov. fairfax sexually assaulted her at the 2004 democratic national convention. another woman, meredith watson, accuses the lieutenant governor of raping her in 2000 when the two attended duke university. fairfax has denied both claims. the event page for the symposium lists dr. tyson as one of two panelists. she will focus on “connections between sexual violence and the persistent structural inequality that disproportionately impact women and girls.” it’s scheduled for 5:30 p.m. pst on tuesday, february 12. original article source...

so many times people only show their good side, and their best moments. unfortunately the effects of that is every time someone gets on social media they automatically feel worse about themselves when they get off. i wish everyone would just be real and show the world who they really are so everybody can realize that they are trying to be something or someone that not even real. you would be surprised what edits and filters can do. i have seen women on the gram and  on tv in real life and did not even recognize them. i know a lot of women and men wanna fake it till you make it. that why people don’t like to do live videos or facetime, bc what it looks like in pictures is not what it is in real life. i encourage you to look at yourself in the mirror and tell yourself how beautiful you are. love yourself more and be authentic to yourself and you won’t have to fake it for the gram. the bi product of self love is power. once you love yourself all the power is in your hand. nobody can take what’s yours and that’s self love and you are the only one who can give to to yourself. be blessed today!

text: അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ഇഷ്ടമായിരുന്നു.അല്ല,അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിന്റെ നാടകങ്ങളും സിനിമകളും ഇഷ്ടമായിരുന്നു.ജീവിതത്തിലെ സോങ് ജി ഉൻ മയക്കുമരുന്ന്കേസിലെ പ്രതിയാണെന്നും #metoo വിവാദവീരനാണെന്നും അതിനാൽ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ തനിക്കിഷ്ടമല്ലെന്നും അവൾ പറഞ്ഞിരുന്നത് അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനോടുള്ള ഇഷ്ടം കുറയ്ക്കാൻ ഒരു കാരണമേ ആയിരുന്നില്ല.അവൻ ഇഷ്‌ടപ്പെട്ടത് ജീവിതത്തിലെ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ആയിരുന്നില്ല;'മിയാന്വേ ബോക്ജൂഷി'യിൽ കുട്ടിക്കാലം മുതൽ താൻ പ്രണയിച്ചിരുന്ന തന്റെ കൂട്ടുകാരി മറ്റൊരാളെ വിവാഹം ചെയ്ത രാത്രി സിഞ്ചെൻലാ നദിക്കരയിൽ നിന്ന് പൊട്ടിക്കരഞ്ഞ് ബഹളം വെച്ചപ്പോൾ  കഷണ്ടിത്തലയൻ പോലീസ്കാരൻ അറസ്റ്റ് ചെയ്ത സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ആയിരുന്നു.'റിഫ്രഷ് മീ'യിൽ തന്നെ മകനെപ്പോലെ കരുതിയിരുന്ന,ഭാവിമരുമകനായി തന്നെ സങ്കൽപിച്ചിരുന്ന,ഒരുമിച്ചു പഠിക്കുന്ന കൂട്ടുകാരിയുടെ അമ്മയായ സ്ത്രീ മരിച്ചയന്ന് മുഖം ചുവന്നു ഞരമ്പ് വലിഞ്ഞു നിലവിളിച്ച് കൊണ്ടിരുന്നവളെ കെട്ടിപ്പിടിച്ച് ശബ്ദം താഴ്ത്തി പൊട്ടിക്കരഞ്ഞ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെയായിരുന്നു.അവളുടെ ഫോൺകോൾ എടുക്കാനോ ഞായറാഴ്ചകളിൽ അവളുടെ  അമ്മയില്ലാക്കുടുംബത്തിനൊപ്പം അത്താഴം കഴിക്കാനോ തോന്നാത്തപ്പോഴൊക്കെ അവൻ വീണ്ടും വീണ്ടും സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിന്റെ അഭിനയം കണ്ട്കൊണ്ടിരുന്നു.അവളെ കാണുമ്പോഴൊക്കെയും പറയാൻ വർഷങ്ങളോളം ശ്രമിച്ചിട്ടും കഴിയാതെ പോയ മൂന്ന് വാക്കുകളുടെ ഭാരത്താൽ ഹൃദയം തളരും.യൂണിവേഴ്സിറ്റി കോളേജിലെ പ്രഗത്ഭനായ സൈക്കോളജി അധ്യാപകന്റെ ഹൃദയമിടിപ്പ് വർദ്ധിക്കും.ഒരു ഭീരുവിന്റെ ആത്മനിന്ദ അവന്റെ സർവ്വ ആത്മവിശ്വാസകോശങ്ങളിലും നിറയും.നിസ്സഹായതയുടെ മൂർദ്ധന്യാവസ്ഥയിൽ അവന് കരയാൻ തോന്നും;വെള്ളം കുടിക്കാൻ തോന്നും.അന്ന് പക്ഷേ അങ്ങനെയൊന്നുമുണ്ടായില്ല.കല്യാണപ്പെണ്ണിന്റെ ആങ്ങളയോ ഇളയച്ഛനോ അടുത്ത കൂട്ടുകാരനോ ചെയ്യേണ്ട വെഡിങ് ഹോസ്റ്റ് സ്ഥാനമേറ്റെടുത്ത് 'lets welcome the bride and the groom' എന്ന് മൈക്കിലൂടെ പറഞ്ഞപ്പോൾ അവന്റെ സ്വരമിടറിയില്ല.വെഡിങ് റിങ് അണിയിച്ച ശേഷം താനല്ലാതെ മറ്റൊരാളെ ഉമ്മ വെച്ച അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും പണ്ട് മറ്റൊരാൾക്കൊപ്പം അവൾ ഡേറ്റിന് പോയപ്പോൾ അനുഭവപ്പെട്ട ദേഷ്യം അവന് തോന്നിയില്ല.വരൻ ഗോങ് യുവിന്റെ കാറിൽ കയറും മുമ്പ് അച്ഛനെയും ചേട്ടനെയും കെട്ടിപ്പിടിച്ച് കണ്ണ് തുടച്ച ശേഷം"കുമാഓ ചിങ്കുയാ"(നന്ദി കൂട്ടുകാരാ)എന്ന് പറഞ്ഞു തന്നെ വട്ടം ചുറ്റിപ്പിടിച്ച് അവൾ ഏതാനും നിമിഷങ്ങളോളം നിന്നപ്പോഴും അവന്റെ ആത്മനിയന്ത്രണ ഞരമ്പുകൾ പൊട്ടി ചോരയൊലിച്ചില്ല.വെള്ള ഗൗൺ അല്പം പൊക്കി കാറിനുള്ളിൽ കയറിയിരുന്നു തിരിഞ്ഞു നോക്കിയ അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും അവന്റെ മുഖത്തെ ജെന്റിൽമാൻ പുഞ്ചിരിക്ക് ഇളക്കം തട്ടിയില്ല.കൂടെ നിഴൽ പോലെ ഇരുപത്തൊന്ന് വർഷം 👇👇👇

tweet_full: അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ഇഷ്ടമായിരുന്നു.അല്ല,അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിന്റെ നാടകങ്ങളും സിനിമകളും ഇഷ്ടമായിരുന്നു.ജീവിതത്തിലെ സോങ് ജി ഉൻ മയക്കുമരുന്ന്കേസിലെ പ്രതിയാണെന്നും #metoo വിവാദവീരനാണെന്നും അതിനാൽ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ തനിക്കിഷ്ടമല്ലെന്നും അവൾ പറഞ്ഞിരുന്നത് അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനോടുള്ള ഇഷ്ടം കുറയ്ക്കാൻ ഒരു കാരണമേ ആയിരുന്നില്ല.അവൻ ഇഷ്‌ടപ്പെട്ടത് ജീവിതത്തിലെ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ആയിരുന്നില്ല;'മിയാന്വേ ബോക്ജൂഷി'യിൽ കുട്ടിക്കാലം മുതൽ താൻ പ്രണയിച്ചിരുന്ന തന്റെ കൂട്ടുകാരി മറ്റൊരാളെ വിവാഹം ചെയ്ത രാത്രി സിഞ്ചെൻലാ നദിക്കരയിൽ നിന്ന് പൊട്ടിക്കരഞ്ഞ് ബഹളം വെച്ചപ്പോൾ  കഷണ്ടിത്തലയൻ പോലീസ്കാരൻ അറസ്റ്റ് ചെയ്ത സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ആയിരുന്നു.'റിഫ്രഷ് മീ'യിൽ തന്നെ മകനെപ്പോലെ കരുതിയിരുന്ന,ഭാവിമരുമകനായി തന്നെ സങ്കൽപിച്ചിരുന്ന,ഒരുമിച്ചു പഠിക്കുന്ന കൂട്ടുകാരിയുടെ അമ്മയായ സ്ത്രീ മരിച്ചയന്ന് മുഖം ചുവന്നു ഞരമ്പ് വലിഞ്ഞു നിലവിളിച്ച് കൊണ്ടിരുന്നവളെ കെട്ടിപ്പിടിച്ച് ശബ്ദം താഴ്ത്തി പൊട്ടിക്കരഞ്ഞ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെയായിരുന്നു.അവളുടെ ഫോൺകോൾ എടുക്കാനോ ഞായറാഴ്ചകളിൽ അവളുടെ  അമ്മയില്ലാക്കുടുംബത്തിനൊപ്പം അത്താഴം കഴിക്കാനോ തോന്നാത്തപ്പോഴൊക്കെ അവൻ വീണ്ടും വീണ്ടും സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിന്റെ അഭിനയം കണ്ട്കൊണ്ടിരുന്നു.അവളെ കാണുമ്പോഴൊക്കെയും പറയാൻ വർഷങ്ങളോളം ശ്രമിച്ചിട്ടും കഴിയാതെ പോയ മൂന്ന് വാക്കുകളുടെ ഭാരത്താൽ ഹൃദയം തളരും.യൂണിവേഴ്സിറ്റി കോളേജിലെ പ്രഗത്ഭനായ സൈക്കോളജി അധ്യാപകന്റെ ഹൃദയമിടിപ്പ് വർദ്ധിക്കും.ഒരു ഭീരുവിന്റെ ആത്മനിന്ദ അവന്റെ സർവ്വ ആത്മവിശ്വാസകോശങ്ങളിലും നിറയും.നിസ്സഹായതയുടെ മൂർദ്ധന്യാവസ്ഥയിൽ അവന് കരയാൻ തോന്നും;വെള്ളം കുടിക്കാൻ തോന്നും.അന്ന് പക്ഷേ അങ്ങനെയൊന്നുമുണ്ടായില്ല.കല്യാണപ്പെണ്ണിന്റെ ആങ്ങളയോ ഇളയച്ഛനോ അടുത്ത കൂട്ടുകാരനോ ചെയ്യേണ്ട വെഡിങ് ഹോസ്റ്റ് സ്ഥാനമേറ്റെടുത്ത് 'lets welcome the bride and the groom' എന്ന് മൈക്കിലൂടെ പറഞ്ഞപ്പോൾ അവന്റെ സ്വരമിടറിയില്ല.വെഡിങ് റിങ് അണിയിച്ച ശേഷം താനല്ലാതെ മറ്റൊരാളെ ഉമ്മ വെച്ച അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും പണ്ട് മറ്റൊരാൾക്കൊപ്പം അവൾ ഡേറ്റിന് പോയപ്പോൾ അനുഭവപ്പെട്ട ദേഷ്യം അവന് തോന്നിയില്ല.വരൻ ഗോങ് യുവിന്റെ കാറിൽ കയറും മുമ്പ് അച്ഛനെയും ചേട്ടനെയും കെട്ടിപ്പിടിച്ച് കണ്ണ് തുടച്ച ശേഷം"കുമാഓ ചിങ്കുയാ"(നന്ദി കൂട്ടുകാരാ)എന്ന് പറഞ്ഞു തന്നെ വട്ടം ചുറ്റിപ്പിടിച്ച് അവൾ ഏതാനും നിമിഷങ്ങളോളം നിന്നപ്പോഴും അവന്റെ ആത്മനിയന്ത്രണ ഞരമ്പുകൾ പൊട്ടി ചോരയൊലിച്ചില്ല.വെള്ള ഗൗൺ അല്പം പൊക്കി കാറിനുള്ളിൽ കയറിയിരുന്നു തിരിഞ്ഞു നോക്കിയ അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും അവന്റെ മുഖത്തെ ജെന്റിൽമാൻ പുഞ്ചിരിക്ക് ഇളക്കം തട്ടിയില്ല.കൂടെ നിഴൽ പോലെ ഇരുപത്തൊന്ന് വർഷം 👇👇👇

groom' എന്ന് മൈക്കിലൂടെ പറഞ്ഞപ്പോൾ അവന്റെ സ്വരമിടറിയില്ല.വെഡിങ് റിങ് അണിയിച്ച ശേഷം താനല്ലാതെ മറ്റൊരാളെ ഉമ്മ വെച്ച അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും പണ്ട് മറ്റൊരാൾക്കൊപ്പം അവൾ ഡേറ്റിന് പോയപ്പോൾ അനുഭവപ്പെട്ട ദേഷ്യം അവന് തോന്നിയില്ല.വരൻ ഗോങ് യുവിന്റെ കാറിൽ കയറും മുമ്പ് അച്ഛനെയും ചേട്ടനെയും കെട്ടിപ്പിടിച്ച് കണ്ണ് തുടച്ച ശേഷം"കുമാഓ ചിങ്കുയാ"(നന്ദി കൂട്ടുകാരാ)എന്ന് പറഞ്ഞു തന്നെ വട്ടം ചുറ്റിപ്പിടിച്ച് അവൾ ഏതാനും നിമിഷങ്ങളോളം നിന്നപ്പോഴും അവന്റെ ആത്മനിയന്ത്രണ ഞരമ്പുകൾ പൊട്ടി ചോരയൊലിച്ചില്ല.വെള്ള ഗൗൺ അല്പം പൊക്കി കാറിനുള്ളിൽ കയറിയിരുന്നു തിരിഞ്ഞു നോക്കിയ അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും അവന്റെ മുഖത്തെ ജെന്റിൽമാൻ പുഞ്ചിരിക്ക് ഇളക്കം തട്ടിയില്ല.കൂടെ നിഴൽ പോലെ ഇരുപത്തൊന്ന് വർഷം 👇👇👇
stop_filter_tweet: അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ഇഷ്ടമായിരുന്നു.അല്ല , അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിന്റെ നാടകങ്ങളും സിനിമകളും ഇഷ്ടമായിരുന്നു.ജീവിതത്തിലെ സോങ് ജി ഉൻ മയക്കുമരുന്ന്കേസിലെ പ്രതിയാണെന്നും വിവാദവീരനാണെന്നും അതിനാൽ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ തനിക്കിഷ്ടമല്ലെന്നും അവൾ പറഞ്ഞിരുന്നത് അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനോടുള്ള ഇഷ്ടം കുറയ്ക്കാൻ ഒരു കാരണമേ ആയിരുന്നില്ല.അവൻ ഇഷ്‌ടപ്പെട്ടത് ജീവിതത്തിലെ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ആയിരുന്നില്ല ; 'മിയാന്വേ ബോക്ജൂഷി'യിൽ കുട്ടിക്കാലം മുതൽ താൻ പ്രണയിച്ചിരുന്ന തന്റെ കൂട്ടുകാരി മറ്റൊരാളെ വിവാഹം ചെയ്ത രാത്രി സിഞ്ചെൻലാ നദിക്കരയിൽ നിന്ന് പൊട്ടിക്കരഞ്ഞ് ബഹളം വെച്ചപ്പോൾ കഷണ്ടിത്തലയൻ പോലീസ്കാരൻ അറസ്റ്റ് ചെയ്ത സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ആയിരുന്നു . 'റിഫ്രഷ് മീ'യിൽ തന്നെ മകനെപ്പോലെ കരുതിയിരുന്ന , ഭാവിമരുമകനായി തന്നെ സങ്കൽപിച്ചിരുന്ന , ഒരുമിച്ചു പഠിക്കുന്ന കൂട്ടുകാരിയുടെ അമ്മയായ സ്ത്രീ മരിച്ചയന്ന് മുഖം ചുവന്നു ഞരമ്പ് വലിഞ്ഞു നിലവിളിച്ച് കൊണ്ടിരുന്നവളെ കെട്ടിപ്പിടിച്ച് ശബ്ദം താഴ്ത്തി പൊട്ടിക്കരഞ്ഞ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെയായിരുന്നു.അവളുടെ ഫോൺകോൾ എടുക്കാനോ ഞായറാഴ്ചകളിൽ അവളുടെ അമ്മയില്ലാക്കുടുംബത്തിനൊപ്പം അത്താഴം കഴിക്കാനോ തോന്നാത്തപ്പോഴൊക്കെ അവൻ വീണ്ടും വീണ്ടും സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിന്റെ അഭിനയം കണ്ട്കൊണ്ടിരുന്നു.അവളെ കാണുമ്പോഴൊക്കെയും പറയാൻ വർഷങ്ങളോളം ശ്രമിച്ചിട്ടും കഴിയാതെ പോയ മൂന്ന് വാക്കുകളുടെ ഭാരത്താൽ ഹൃദയം തളരും.യൂണിവേഴ്സിറ്റി കോളേജിലെ പ്രഗത്ഭനായ സൈക്കോളജി അധ്യാപകന്റെ ഹൃദയമിടിപ്പ് വർദ്ധിക്കും.ഒരു ഭീരുവിന്റെ ആത്മനിന്ദ അവന്റെ സർവ്വ ആത്മവിശ്വാസകോശങ്ങളിലും നിറയും.നിസ്സഹായതയുടെ മൂർദ്ധന്യാവസ്ഥയിൽ അവന് കരയാൻ തോന്നും ; വെള്ളം കുടിക്കാൻ തോന്നും.അന്ന് പക്ഷേ അങ്ങനെയൊന്നുമുണ്ടായില്ല.കല്യാണപ്പെണ്ണിന്റെ ആങ്ങളയോ ഇളയച്ഛനോ അടുത്ത കൂട്ടുകാരനോ ചെയ്യേണ്ട വെഡിങ് ഹോസ്റ്റ് സ്ഥാനമേറ്റെടുത്ത് 'lets welcome bride groom ' എന്ന് മൈക്കിലൂടെ പറഞ്ഞപ്പോൾ അവന്റെ സ്വരമിടറിയില്ല.വെഡിങ് റിങ് അണിയിച്ച ശേഷം താനല്ലാതെ മറ്റൊരാളെ ഉമ്മ വെച്ച അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും പണ്ട് മറ്റൊരാൾക്കൊപ്പം അവൾ ഡേറ്റിന് പോയപ്പോൾ അനുഭവപ്പെട്ട ദേഷ്യം അവന് തോന്നിയില്ല.വരൻ ഗോങ് യുവിന്റെ കാറിൽ കയറും മുമ്പ് അച്ഛനെയും ചേട്ടനെയും കെട്ടിപ്പിടിച്ച് കണ്ണ് തുടച്ച ശേഷം '' കുമാഓ ചിങ്കുയാ '' ( നന്ദി കൂട്ടുകാരാ ) എന്ന് പറഞ്ഞു തന്നെ വട്ടം ചുറ്റിപ്പിടിച്ച് അവൾ ഏതാനും നിമിഷങ്ങളോളം നിന്നപ്പോഴും അവന്റെ ആത്മനിയന്ത്രണ ഞരമ്പുകൾ പൊട്ടി ചോരയൊലിച്ചില്ല.വെള്ള ഗൗൺ അല്പം പൊക്കി കാറിനുള്ളിൽ കയറിയിരുന്നു തിരിഞ്ഞു നോക്കിയ അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും അവന്റെ മുഖത്തെ ജെന്റിൽമാൻ പുഞ്ചിരിക്ക് ഇളക്കം തട്ടിയില്ല.കൂടെ നിഴൽ പോലെ ഇരുപത്തൊന്ന് വർഷം 👇👇👇
stem_filter: അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ഇഷ്ടമായിരുന്നു.അല്ല , അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിന്റെ നാടകങ്ങളും സിനിമകളും ഇഷ്ടമായിരുന്നു.ജീവിതത്തിലെ സോങ് ജി ഉൻ മയക്കുമരുന്ന്കേസിലെ പ്രതിയാണെന്നും വിവാദവീരനാണെന്നും അതിനാൽ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ തനിക്കിഷ്ടമല്ലെന്നും അവൾ പറഞ്ഞിരുന്നത് അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനോടുള്ള ഇഷ്ടം കുറയ്ക്കാൻ ഒരു കാരണമേ ആയിരുന്നില്ല.അവൻ ഇഷ്‌ടപ്പെട്ടത് ജീവിതത്തിലെ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ആയിരുന്നില്ല ; 'മിയാന്വേ ബോക്ജൂഷി'യിൽ കുട്ടിക്കാലം മുതൽ താൻ പ്രണയിച്ചിരുന്ന തന്റെ കൂട്ടുകാരി മറ്റൊരാളെ വിവാഹം ചെയ്ത രാത്രി സിഞ്ചെൻലാ നദിക്കരയിൽ നിന്ന് പൊട്ടിക്കരഞ്ഞ് ബഹളം വെച്ചപ്പോൾ കഷണ്ടിത്തലയൻ പോലീസ്കാരൻ അറസ്റ്റ് ചെയ്ത സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ആയിരുന്നു . 'റിഫ്രഷ് മീ'യിൽ തന്നെ മകനെപ്പോലെ കരുതിയിരുന്ന , ഭാവിമരുമകനായി തന്നെ സങ്കൽപിച്ചിരുന്ന , ഒരുമിച്ചു പഠിക്കുന്ന കൂട്ടുകാരിയുടെ അമ്മയായ സ്ത്രീ മരിച്ചയന്ന് മുഖം ചുവന്നു ഞരമ്പ് വലിഞ്ഞു നിലവിളിച്ച് കൊണ്ടിരുന്നവളെ കെട്ടിപ്പിടിച്ച് ശബ്ദം താഴ്ത്തി പൊട്ടിക്കരഞ്ഞ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെയായിരുന്നു.അവളുടെ ഫോൺകോൾ എടുക്കാനോ ഞായറാഴ്ചകളിൽ അവളുടെ അമ്മയില്ലാക്കുടുംബത്തിനൊപ്പം അത്താഴം കഴിക്കാനോ തോന്നാത്തപ്പോഴൊക്കെ അവൻ വീണ്ടും വീണ്ടും സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിന്റെ അഭിനയം കണ്ട്കൊണ്ടിരുന്നു.അവളെ കാണുമ്പോഴൊക്കെയും പറയാൻ വർഷങ്ങളോളം ശ്രമിച്ചിട്ടും കഴിയാതെ പോയ മൂന്ന് വാക്കുകളുടെ ഭാരത്താൽ ഹൃദയം തളരും.യൂണിവേഴ്സിറ്റി കോളേജിലെ പ്രഗത്ഭനായ സൈക്കോളജി അധ്യാപകന്റെ ഹൃദയമിടിപ്പ് വർദ്ധിക്കും.ഒരു ഭീരുവിന്റെ ആത്മനിന്ദ അവന്റെ സർവ്വ ആത്മവിശ്വാസകോശങ്ങളിലും നിറയും.നിസ്സഹായതയുടെ മൂർദ്ധന്യാവസ്ഥയിൽ അവന് കരയാൻ തോന്നും ; വെള്ളം കുടിക്കാൻ തോന്നും.അന്ന് പക്ഷേ അങ്ങനെയൊന്നുമുണ്ടായില്ല.കല്യാണപ്പെണ്ണിന്റെ ആങ്ങളയോ ഇളയച്ഛനോ അടുത്ത കൂട്ടുകാരനോ ചെയ്യേണ്ട വെഡിങ് ഹോസ്റ്റ് സ്ഥാനമേറ്റെടുത്ത് 'let welcom bride groom ' എന്ന് മൈക്കിലൂടെ പറഞ്ഞപ്പോൾ അവന്റെ സ്വരമിടറിയില്ല.വെഡിങ് റിങ് അണിയിച്ച ശേഷം താനല്ലാതെ മറ്റൊരാളെ ഉമ്മ വെച്ച അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും പണ്ട് മറ്റൊരാൾക്കൊപ്പം അവൾ ഡേറ്റിന് പോയപ്പോൾ അനുഭവപ്പെട്ട ദേഷ്യം അവന് തോന്നിയില്ല.വരൻ ഗോങ് യുവിന്റെ കാറിൽ കയറും മുമ്പ് അച്ഛനെയും ചേട്ടനെയും കെട്ടിപ്പിടിച്ച് കണ്ണ് തുടച്ച ശേഷം `` കുമാഓ ചിങ്കുയാ `` ( നന്ദി കൂട്ടുകാരാ ) എന്ന് പറഞ്ഞു തന്നെ വട്ടം ചുറ്റിപ്പിടിച്ച് അവൾ ഏതാനും നിമിഷങ്ങളോളം നിന്നപ്പോഴും അവന്റെ ആത്മനിയന്ത്രണ ഞരമ്പുകൾ പൊട്ടി ചോരയൊലിച്ചില്ല.വെള്ള ഗൗൺ അല്പം പൊക്കി കാറിനുള്ളിൽ കയറിയിരുന്നു തിരിഞ്ഞു നോക്കിയ അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും അവന്റെ മുഖത്തെ ജെന്റിൽമാൻ പുഞ്ചിരിക്ക് ഇളക്കം തട്ടിയില്ല.കൂടെ നിഴൽ പോലെ ഇരുപത്തൊന്ന് വർഷം 👇👇👇
lemma_filter: അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ഇഷ്ടമായിരുന്നു.അല്ല , അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിന്റെ നാടകങ്ങളും സിനിമകളും ഇഷ്ടമായിരുന്നു.ജീവിതത്തിലെ സോങ് ജി ഉൻ മയക്കുമരുന്ന്കേസിലെ പ്രതിയാണെന്നും വിവാദവീരനാണെന്നും അതിനാൽ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ തനിക്കിഷ്ടമല്ലെന്നും അവൾ പറഞ്ഞിരുന്നത് അവന് സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനോടുള്ള ഇഷ്ടം കുറയ്ക്കാൻ ഒരു കാരണമേ ആയിരുന്നില്ല.അവൻ ഇഷ്‌ടപ്പെട്ടത് ജീവിതത്തിലെ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ആയിരുന്നില്ല ; 'മിയാന്വേ ബോക്ജൂഷി'യിൽ കുട്ടിക്കാലം മുതൽ താൻ പ്രണയിച്ചിരുന്ന തന്റെ കൂട്ടുകാരി മറ്റൊരാളെ വിവാഹം ചെയ്ത രാത്രി സിഞ്ചെൻലാ നദിക്കരയിൽ നിന്ന് പൊട്ടിക്കരഞ്ഞ് ബഹളം വെച്ചപ്പോൾ കഷണ്ടിത്തലയൻ പോലീസ്കാരൻ അറസ്റ്റ് ചെയ്ത സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെ ആയിരുന്നു . 'റിഫ്രഷ് മീ'യിൽ തന്നെ മകനെപ്പോലെ കരുതിയിരുന്ന , ഭാവിമരുമകനായി തന്നെ സങ്കൽപിച്ചിരുന്ന , ഒരുമിച്ചു പഠിക്കുന്ന കൂട്ടുകാരിയുടെ അമ്മയായ സ്ത്രീ മരിച്ചയന്ന് മുഖം ചുവന്നു ഞരമ്പ് വലിഞ്ഞു നിലവിളിച്ച് കൊണ്ടിരുന്നവളെ കെട്ടിപ്പിടിച്ച് ശബ്ദം താഴ്ത്തി പൊട്ടിക്കരഞ്ഞ സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിനെയായിരുന്നു.അവളുടെ ഫോൺകോൾ എടുക്കാനോ ഞായറാഴ്ചകളിൽ അവളുടെ അമ്മയില്ലാക്കുടുംബത്തിനൊപ്പം അത്താഴം കഴിക്കാനോ തോന്നാത്തപ്പോഴൊക്കെ അവൻ വീണ്ടും വീണ്ടും സോങ് ജി ഉന്നിന്റെ അഭിനയം കണ്ട്കൊണ്ടിരുന്നു.അവളെ കാണുമ്പോഴൊക്കെയും പറയാൻ വർഷങ്ങളോളം ശ്രമിച്ചിട്ടും കഴിയാതെ പോയ മൂന്ന് വാക്കുകളുടെ ഭാരത്താൽ ഹൃദയം തളരും.യൂണിവേഴ്സിറ്റി കോളേജിലെ പ്രഗത്ഭനായ സൈക്കോളജി അധ്യാപകന്റെ ഹൃദയമിടിപ്പ് വർദ്ധിക്കും.ഒരു ഭീരുവിന്റെ ആത്മനിന്ദ അവന്റെ സർവ്വ ആത്മവിശ്വാസകോശങ്ങളിലും നിറയും.നിസ്സഹായതയുടെ മൂർദ്ധന്യാവസ്ഥയിൽ അവന് കരയാൻ തോന്നും ; വെള്ളം കുടിക്കാൻ തോന്നും.അന്ന് പക്ഷേ അങ്ങനെയൊന്നുമുണ്ടായില്ല.കല്യാണപ്പെണ്ണിന്റെ ആങ്ങളയോ ഇളയച്ഛനോ അടുത്ത കൂട്ടുകാരനോ ചെയ്യേണ്ട വെഡിങ് ഹോസ്റ്റ് സ്ഥാനമേറ്റെടുത്ത് 'lets welcome bride groom ' എന്ന് മൈക്കിലൂടെ പറഞ്ഞപ്പോൾ അവന്റെ സ്വരമിടറിയില്ല.വെഡിങ് റിങ് അണിയിച്ച ശേഷം താനല്ലാതെ മറ്റൊരാളെ ഉമ്മ വെച്ച അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും പണ്ട് മറ്റൊരാൾക്കൊപ്പം അവൾ ഡേറ്റിന് പോയപ്പോൾ അനുഭവപ്പെട്ട ദേഷ്യം അവന് തോന്നിയില്ല.വരൻ ഗോങ് യുവിന്റെ കാറിൽ കയറും മുമ്പ് അച്ഛനെയും ചേട്ടനെയും കെട്ടിപ്പിടിച്ച് കണ്ണ് തുടച്ച ശേഷം  കുമാഓ ചിങ്കുയാ  ( നന്ദി കൂട്ടുകാരാ ) എന്ന് പറഞ്ഞു തന്നെ വട്ടം ചുറ്റിപ്പിടിച്ച് അവൾ ഏതാനും നിമിഷങ്ങളോളം നിന്നപ്പോഴും അവന്റെ ആത്മനിയന്ത്രണ ഞരമ്പുകൾ പൊട്ടി ചോരയൊലിച്ചില്ല.വെള്ള ഗൗൺ അല്പം പൊക്കി കാറിനുള്ളിൽ കയറിയിരുന്നു തിരിഞ്ഞു നോക്കിയ അവളെ കണ്ടിട്ടും അവന്റെ മുഖത്തെ ജെന്റിൽമാൻ പുഞ്ചിരിക്ക് ഇളക്കം തട്ടിയില്ല.കൂടെ നിഴൽ പോലെ ഇരുപത്തൊന്ന് വർഷം 👇👇👇

text:
#yosumo ➕ . porque un año más reivindicamos la necesidad e importancia de positivizar a la 👩 mujer. porqué no sólo el 8 de marzo 🗓 tenemos que mostrar cómo y qué somos. porqué cada día somos. somos una buena noticia🗞️. tú, ¿sumas? 
en 24 días es el día de la mujer ♀️la mujer… ¿qué está pasando con la mujer? sin duda, últimamente somos noticia… sin parar. y esos sería una buena noticia si no fuera porque lo han vuelto a hacer: estamos siendo una vez más víctimas de la sociedad masculinizada.👎 como mujer y como periodista estoy decidida a darle un giro a esto. con vuestra ayuda💪. porque esto lo hemos de cambiar entre toda/os. las mujeres somos una buena noticia: no somos sólo acoso sexual, #metoo brecha salarial, conciliación solo para nosotras, violencia de género, techo de cristal, … sin duda, hay que seguir trabajando para que todo esto deje de existir…
pero 🚺 mujeres y hombres 🚹 de la sala: está en nuestras manos cambiarlo. en positivo ➕. las mujeres somos infinidad de cosas positivas. os lo voy a demostrar. os lo vamos a demostrar. os invito, mujeres y hombres, a que entre todos♀️♂️ generemos un nueva corriente, una nueva actitud, una nueva ola de noticias sobre la mujer: y el 8 de marzo compartiremos cómo hombres y mujeres hemos positivizado a las mujer. #yosumo #ellasuma. no queremos seguir siendo la excusa negativa para que los medios llenen sus páginas, canales y ondas. #liderandoelcambio capitaneado por nosotras, las mujeres. acompañadas por aquellos hombres que sí, saben, creen, apuestan y potencian el valor de ser mujer. porque las mujeres somos una buena noticia. #yosumo por todas las mujeres del mundo. #somosconsentidasenpositivo

como organización estudiantil, nos solidarizamos con las compañeras denunciantes y exigimos a las autoridades que se tomen, con firmeza, las medidas correspondientes con los docentes implicados; y se estipulen los protocolos a seguir para erradicar la el acoso, los ataques sexuales y cualquier tipo de violencia hacia las estudiantes.
.

text:
yesterday marked the introduction of the highly anticipated maternity and obs/gyn module. being one of the aspects of medicine that particularly interests me, i couldn't wait to start learning about it. 
we covered a range of topics in our 8 hour day from gynaecological emergencies to sexual assault and i was left with so much respect for all midwives. 
one topic that was particularly focused upon was how to approach those who have been sexually assaulted. the fragility and vulnerability one is left with after such an event is horrific. it's shameful to think that in our constantly progressing society, this still happens and people still refuse to talk about it. it's still covered and hidden, and those who have been the victims are left to suffer while the perpetrators uphold their false, hypocritical respect. 
we all have a duty of care towards each other. if you notice anyone you're close to acting differently, shying away or refusing to talk then be there for them, refer them to helplines, show that you care. no one deserves to feel like that and those who cause it, should be caught. 
rape crisis
helpline: 0808 802 9999

victim support
supportline: 0808 168 9111
https://www.victimsupport.org.uk

the survivors trust
helpline: 0808 801 0818
thesurvivorstrust.org

text:
inspired from what most of us have experienced..
the goal of this project is to listen and give a voice to the victims of sexual abuse. .
from simple words, lack of respect, abuse , manipulation and extreme behaviors. as an artist i will try my best to canalise these feelings.. and put them on paper.
if you want to share something with me, feel welcome. this might well be a lifelong project.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: every successful team knows that their achievement depends on a community of persons working together. we are thankful to our team of creatives, logistics, media, security, and volunteers for giving their best and pulling off something we could only do together. to the celebrities, writers, musicians, poets, organizations politicians, sponsors, and influencers, thank you for joining our force. by adding your colors to our festivity, you have bravely stood by us as we fight against the evils in our society. after sparking these important conversations, we hand it over to you change makers to keep the conversation going and not let it die. our volunteers gave their heart and soul to perform their duties and were remarkable. we are thankful to our wonderful audience for being so civil, following and understanding the reason behind our rules and regulations and for turning up in huge amounts to attentively listen to the sessions and joining us whole heartedly in the festivity. an increasing number of women and girls joined us and showed ownership of this festival. we hope this was a small but impact full win for all survivors of harassment and abuse regardless of their gender. we would especially like to thank our media and newspapers for doing a mature coverage of the festival and capturing the whole essence of festivity while giving the much needed importance to our theme without unnecessarily scandalizing anything. the security team helped us create a delightful and safe environment for all just how we imagined, so kudos to them. thanks to our audience sending us massive love and respect from all over the world. we just re-ignited a fire that was being stopped from sustaining in pakistan by powerful & influential people focused on their personal gains. we hope each individual who took a burning lamp with them, passes it on to others so these voices are not silenced again. until next time - #lahooti #lahootimelo #anodetowomen #metoo #ibelieveher #thesketchesband #lahootimelo2019 📸 @as.photography.pk

this isn't the post i was planning to write for the international day of the women and girls in science, but today was just one of those days. work, kids, laundry and a colorful variety of mundane life problems… i'm exhausted. i sat down in front of my computer and resumed my perpetual inner struggle: should i work to meet my deadline? write the post? early night so tomorrow i’m more productive? guilt. so i decided to write about this.
.
when people ask me ‘how do you cope with 4 kids?’ i always reply: i don’t, i’m very tired. but this is part of being a parent and you get used to it. when you reach #4 you don’t remember what is was like before. and you know, i love my kids.
.
what's hard is the guilt that comes with the pressure to be a perfect mum. at this stage i care less because i know what matters. a perfect 3-tier princess birthday cake doesn’t matter.
.
this pressure for perfection is every woman’s curse. we have to work 10x harder (minorities 50x harder) as a man to get the same recognition. incompetent (white) men succeed, overqualified women lag behind. and we strive to be perfect, we try so hard… and it’s exhausting.
.
we need to end the double standards and biases, but we also must release women from the pressure and the guilt. and the way we portray role models isn’t helping. take marie curie for ex. how can we ever measure up to that? she was a superwoman! two kids, two nobel prizes, a war hero… how is this possible?
.
but she wasn’t a superwoman (i wrote about this on my website, link in bio). she was very tired. she felt guilty when she was at work and when she was with her children. she always felt she wasn’t doing enough. just like me, just like every woman today. but i would never had known curie felt like this if i hadn’t read a book about her, because most her biographies don’t mention it.
.
how do we break the pressure/guilt cycle that discourages girls and women from pursuing and staying in stem careers? we need relatable role models to show young girls that despite the hurdles, self-doubt, guilt, exhaustion... we can do it.
.
the #womeninstem on instagram are doing an amazing job breaking stereotypes, so let's celebrate them today!
.
.

text:
i can’t even tell you how many times i heard that when i smile my eyes look really small or that my teeth look ugly or that my smiles looks weird it got to a point where i just stopped smiling all together because that was all i could think about but then people started saying that i should smile more and i looked so much prettier when i smiled or even that i didn’t want to look like “one of those depressed shitheads” (yes this was an actual phrase that i heard an actual person say in 2018) so i started smiling more. what i mean is: don’t ever tell people that their happiness is ugly, stupid, childish... it’s their happiness and they deserve to show it. - ✨

text_retweet:
#repost @makeequal with @get_repost
・・・
// webbutbildning mot sexuella kränkningar // vi är oerhört stolta över att ha varit delaktiga i backa – initiativet för en skola fri från sexuella kränkningar. på backa.org släpps idag en webbutbildning som tillgängliggör kunskap och praktiska verktyg så att fler ska kunna bidra till att förebygga sexuella kränkningar och trakasserier i skolan. gör utbildningen på www.backa.org och var med och skapa konkret förändring! där hittar du även backainitiativets kampanjfilm, skapad av den duktiga regissören @jakobstrom. #backainitiativet @backaorg ➡️ ni vet väl att ni även kan anlita oss för att genomföra en utbildning på er skola? vi var med och genomförde backa-turnén som besökte 208 högstadium och gymnasium i hela sverige i höstas.

i en sådan utbildning hjälper vi er att kartlägga och ta fram en handlingsplan för er skola samt lyfter ämnen såsom normer, machokulturer och hur vi alla kan vara en del i att motverka sexuella trakasserier. maila till kim@makeequal.se för att få veta mer! #makeequal #metoo

text:

from ➡️ @thegameologist 
my little experiment to turn a well drink, like a whiskey and coke, into more of a craft cocktail with some added flavors. also been seeing some people on here being pretty creative with their vessels so gave me the bright idea for this one. cheers!
===
craft whiskey & coke
===
2 oz. whiskey
1 oz. coca cola syrup
3/4 oz. lime juice
mint leaves
raspberries
===
muddle raspberries and mint leaves in shaker. add in other ingredients and shake with ice. strain over crushed ice into glass and top with more ice.
===

text:
“red shoes.” innocence. 
a survivor of sexual assault, holding a picture of herself just before her first sexual assault. she was raped over 50 times in her lifetime by boys and men up to 30 years older than her – assaults that were never reported to the police. she has been struggling with post-traumatic stress disorder ever since. 
she survived. she broke the cycle. she’s my hero.

text:
next wednesday february 20th @ 7:30pm: i may have left america, but i still support planned parenthood and fighting sexual assault (and you should too). i’ll be performing one of these stunning and important pieces, alongside some other fabulous women and performers. if you love me, come watch. if you don’t love me, come watch anyway because this is bigger than me. ************************************************************
in the lead up to the 2016 election, 19 brave women came forward with stories of sexual harassment and assault by the man who is now the pussy grabber-in-chief. almost exactly a year later, as the #metoo movement began to spark real change, we were dismayed and furious to see that these women who had paved the way to #metoo had been largely forgotten or reduced to a number.

as theater-makers, we knew we could help to share their stories so that their courage would continue to reverberate throughout the country. tonight, we get to bring these stories to life, harnessing the power of theater to ignite conversation, create community, make change and spread awareness of harassment and assault.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
i’m a survivor. and i know so many of you are too. and sometimes just sharing that over and over again  is necessary, healing, and exhausting.
i’ve been sharing my story in a fairly public domain by performing muthaland since 2015, when i first started writing it. i never thought i would still be sharing it in 2019. after meeting so many other amazing survivors by doing this work... i suppose i started to believe the conversations were getting more public, more voices were being heard, and starting to feel like this story would finally become irrelevant. i wish that every time i share it. that one day an entire audience will see the show and think, “that’s ridiculous. why would someone ever violate another human in such a base and disgusting way?”
but, we’re not there yet. and it breaks my heart. i’m leaving to go perform muthaland at hope college in michigan this week. and it’s been awhile since i’ve picked up the script. when i go out on the road it’s literally a solo-show in every aspect. i just bring my 2 suitcases, cue lab on my laptop and i work with wonderful people there to tech for a few hours...and then there is an audience.
i feel healthy doing the show. i have self-care practices in place. and i know there  is so much power in sharing your story with the community. 
but as i start to get back into it, there is always a moment where i realize while it is “just a play,” it’s also my real life. and different parts of the play hit me differently at times.
for whatever reason this time i’m angry. that’s not an emotion that comes up often for me. i feel broken, exhausted and mad. mostly because  i know for every time i share my story there are thousands of women who don’t have the privilege to. yes, i know that me being american, having had parents that believed me, and being in a position to escape the man that assaulted me, to leave that country...gave me greater freedom and privilege to speak out. 
and i just want to acknowledge that. and acknowledge all my sisters out there. and send you love. and i hope you know you are not alone. 
and i also acknowledge that a decade later i still hurt from it. and that is okay. (continued in comments)

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
i used to be so determined to succeed at all cost. .

when i look back at the person i was, i don’t like what i see.  i was all about making money because i never had any growing up. .

i was fearful of loosing it so i didn’t spend much of it.  now, i’m not saying you should spend everything you make. but you should definitely think about enjoying some of it. .

on my trip to poland i decided i was going to spoil myself.  i love to set goals and reward myself in turn.  so this trip had plenty of great rooms, great meals, a few fun outfits and some spa treatments. .

guess what.  it made me happy. .

i still value making and saving money but since mike passed these little presents to myself do a lot for my wounded soul. .

check out my digs on the next slides!➡️➡️➡️➡️➡️➡️

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters
