text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
сила внутри нас
⠀
всем привет, друзья! меня зовут алсу, и я хочу познакомить вас со своей деятельностью:
⠀
◽я будущий психолог, учусь в школе петрушина с.в.
(несмотря на то, что я только учусь, я сама посещала и посещаю психолога и мне есть чем с вами поделиться)
⠀
◽я специалист по access bars/body.
 это одно из направлений в телесной терапии: а именно работа с барами( точками на голове- энергетический массаж) и работа с телом( телесная терапия).
⠀
телесная терапия даёт возможность человеку выйти за пределы своих ограничений и страхов. отпустить все то, что ему мешает.
⠀
на личном опыте я столкнулась с тем, что вроде бы проговаривала проблему с психологом, осознавала все,но не ощущала чувства легкости, или оно быстро уходило. я ощущала, что из тела блок не уходит, психосоматика оставалась. мое тело болело, и проблема так и не была решена.
⠀
тело хотело, чтобы его трогали.
⠀
тело хотело внимания
⠀
только представьте, как вы чувствуете себя при стрессе, вспомните, что происходит с вашим телом. а если вы так живёте год, два или десять лет...
⠀
только представьте, что стало с вашим телом..
⠀
сейчас жизнь в стрессе считается обычным явлением, и тело уже не помнит, как это - быть расслабленным.
⠀
я почувствовала колоссальный прорыв, когда стала работать ещё и с телом.
испробовав на себе и увидев результат, я поняла, что это работает.
⠀
и сейчас я хочу помочь вам♥️
⠀
а что ещё возможно?
⠀

text:
•”we are linked not ranked”• -gloria steinem
-
i’ve read nearly every word @gloriasteinem has ever written. getting to meet her felt outer body- i had so many questions and at the same time felt like i couldn’t even speak (thankfully, i did 😌).
-
after talking with her i walked away with real insight but what was most piercing about the ten minutes i spent with her was her •presence•. she was memorably present in the conversation...she listened intently, and spoke without any pretense whatsoever. she was utterly secure with the person she was and brought her full self to each and every moment.
-
this post probably sounds a bit melodramatic but it was a really unique experience- i’ve only met a few people with that kind of complete presence in my entire life. i realized after our exchange, that sort of spirit + self confidence is such a gift to ourselves and to those we are with. 🖤 #changemaker #troublemaker #historymaker @makerswomen

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
sometimes we do not realize that it takes a lot to speak out and to take action on very sensitive topics, such as domestic violence and sexual assault.  as a society we need to understand that people may be afraid to speak out due to embarrassment, retaliation, and a fear that no one will believe them. 
i was lucky enough to get a @createcultivate ticket to see the @amazon screening of lorena and to hear her speak on a panel today. in 1994 lorena gallo went on trial for cutting off her then husband’s penis out of self defense for rape. john bobbitt’s penis was surgically reattached and he has even received multiple battery charges from other women years after this trial. 
lorena is brave enough to share her story and to bring awareness about domestic violence and sexual assault victims. she shows that she does not let anything define her, which brings even more attention to the #metoo movement we have today. unfortunately, back in the 1990s her story often got lost due to dick jokes and also because she was a latina immigrant.

this documentary series also brings into thoughts of how we can better support victims in their journey for  justice and healing mentally instead of asking them why they took so long to report their abusers. 
you can catch the @jordanpeele lorena bobbitt four part documentary series on @amazonprimevideo on 2/15/19. @ndvhofficial is also available via call/chat 24/7/365 at 1−800−799−7233 and https://www.thehotline.org/. 👱🏽‍♀️👩🏻‍🦱👭👩🏽 •
•
•

#truecrime #domesticviolence #mentalhealth #sexualassault #womensrights #believesurvivors #youarenotalone #feminism #womensupportingwomen #timesup #trauma #lorenaseries

en france en 2018, on estime à moins de 10% les personnes qui osent porter plainte pour ces faits. voilà par exemple à quelle autre forme de violence doivent faire face les victimes lorsqu’elles trouvent le courage de parler...
plus de 500 témoignages accablants déjà recueillis en quelques jours.

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i have spent my life eating at the kid’s table—never quite certain if it’s okay for me to be with the grown-ups.  if i let my guard down and neglect to censor my conversation and behavior, i retreat as soon as i realize my misstep (who does she think she is?) i, like many survivors, struggle with taking up space.  i spent too many years trying to be invisible.  so incredibly grateful for people who make me feel valued. they tide me over while i learn to value myself. it is with these accepting souls that i most feel at home in my space.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
day 12..i have a bunch of new friends “followers” and i thought i’d introduce myself and explain what i’m doing on here..
.
.
my name is molly and i decided while in ireland in may 2018 that i needed to change/fix my life. i just started this journey in january only 12 days ago. i’ve had a few challenges in my life and i’ve never really put in the work to fix the issues that came from those challenges. .
.
i’m using social media to keep myself accountable. i quit everything in my life and this time i’m not going to let that happen. i’m losing weight (40 pounds down total so far) and working through all the crap i’ve been through. .
.
what have i faced? ..well being overweight obviously, #metoo which caused me to have ptsd (diagnosed in 2018) and i have a rare illness called pseudo tumor cerebri..to which there is no cure & causes me to be in chronic pain and to top all that off...i turned to alcohol to numb it all. wow, i’m a mess 😬 there will be more on all that to come. .
.
sharing all this isn’t easy but i know there are so many people out there just like me. life isn’t perfect and can get messy, for anyone. it’s nice to not feel alone in struggle and maybe by me taking this very uncomfortable leap i might help someone else. so it’s bound to be a bumpy ride but thank you for tuning in and by the way i’m an open book..have a question? just ask! .
.
#day12 #metoo #ptsdawareness #invisableillness #weightlossmotivation #pseudotumorcerebri #anxiety #depressionhelp #myyearofchange #thisismycomeback #2019

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
🌺 meet one of 20+ presenters at boundless self-love retreat 2019: invoking the warrior woman, melaina faranda
✨
melania has been working with the divine feminine and women’s mysteries for over twenty years. she has founded and facilitated numerous women’s and girls’ circles and events, is a red tent facilitator, co-creator of the priestesses of gaia path and has written forty plus books for young people. she is passionate about being with and in sacred natural water.
✨
melania’s planned workshop is called “wild water witching.” ✨
water holds memory and water is life. water cleanses, heals, and blesses. in our work, we will be honouring the element of water within and without and ways to enter the other world through water. ✨
during this workshop you will be discovering and connecting with your personal water ally, and communing with the water witch and water goddess in her various guises through a guided drumming journey, then learning how to magically bless and charge water for use in sacred ceremony and healing. sacred waters from all over the world will be ritually mixed in our chalice, including water from mary’s house in ephesus, chalice well in glastonbury, and the delphic spring in delphos. you will learn a unique technique for healing others with this water. please bring a small bottle of sacred water from your home or from a water place which is special to you. at the end of the workshop you will be refilling with the magically merged water to take home for your personal sacred practice.
✨
this session will be cleansing, healing and introduce women to sacred ways to deepen their relationship to water in their own lives.
🌺
you are most welcome to join our tribe of beautiful women at the 2019 boundless self love retreat :: invoking the warrior woman, where we will be creating a circle of connectivity helps eliminate isolation. at this retreat you will experience empowering workshops and activities, meet awesome people and have to to feel, be heard and be fully seen. absolute soul food!
✨
🖤 see more about this event and ticket info in our bio link 🖤
✨
red tent australia is a kind, caring, supporting, national, non-profit, social enterprise.
✨

text:
a running list:

1. mercy has the flu. i am trying not to freak out about it, as i’m generally not an anxious person. but i am (perhaps irrationally) shook by this, on account of how small and vulnerable and unlikely to eat vegetables she is. is the flu my fault? should i have vaccinated? made her eat more broccoli? shunned her from the two bouncy house birthday parties we survived the week prior? 
2. will i ever know the answers to these questions? (of course not - mom brain does not concern itself with such nonsense as rational thought bc #fakenews) 
3. steve has been traveling for more than three weeks off and on since we’ve moved into our new home. this is because he is a freaking rockstar three who is killing it at bringing his gifts to the church right now despite such a crazy painful season. i am so proud of him. and thankful. and also? so so tired. a moment of silence for our sanity, which took leave somewhere in week two. #blessit
4. there are scorpions here.
5. with every new #metoo post and #churchtoo article that comes out, i am both stricken with grief and entirely reignited in my commitment to truth and justice for victims of sexual assault. especially at the hands of ‘leaders’ of the church. 
6. i have never been more thankful for the sunshine. it comes out every day here, you guys. every damn day, like a friend you can count on. at one point, i may have actually curled up in a sunny spot that stretched across the tile and cried a little. 
7. there is no easy way. no right way. no one way. not for any of us. there is only the slowness and softness of a place that allows us to listen to the whispers of a soul deeply in love with jesus. with love. with the love who makes us all. i’m learning how to trust that love again and it is scary and wild and absolutely gorgeous. 
8. thank god for his ability to be bigger than any of us could imagine. bigger than our books and our boxes and our buildings. big enough to surprise and delight us for all of our days. may we allow ourselves the grace of that delight. #amen
• 📸 credit: sleepless nights and general parental paranoia with special guest scorpion phobia.

text:
malini kochupillai, the delhi-based photographer, also pointed out that while people talk amongst themselves, there is no culture of raising critical concerns. even when questions are raised the natural defensive response is, “they asked me, i was given consent.” she adds, “the real question should be to interrogate why photographers are able to produce work without thinking about the consequences. there was an utter, shameful lack of criticality in ways in which shantaram’s work was promoted from the get-go. [but] more than shantaram’s work, it points to how the art world talks about and promotes specific artists and artworks. this is problematic and symptomatic of the whole industry. we can’t just critique shantaram, he is just one of the many. we have to question a system that continues to make works like shantaram’s possible.”
.
.

text:
for anyone who has experienced people you love betraying you, turning their back when you told them about your abuse, looked away, didn’t believe you, listened when told they shouldn’t associate with you any longer because it would hurt your chances for an opportunity and especially those who took the side of your abuser for personal gain, for a “second chance” or even money, i feel you. you’re not alone. it hurts.
.
you actually never needed them. you had the power within you all along. hurting people, hurt people. with no regard or cost when there is personal gain. it’s an act of fear and lack of courage.
.
when you stand in your truth, remember not everyone is strong enough to stand with you. and that’s ok. because you don’t need a hundred superficial relationships in your life with people who will betray best friends at the drop of a dime. they did it to you and they will do it to others without thinking twice. you need a handful or two of people who truly have your back. to laugh with. to cry with. to lean on anytime.
.
you’re not alone if you’ve experienced this. many people have reached out and told me stories of betrayal. when you speak a hard truth, remember not everyone is brave enough to stand with you. you don’t need them. your voice is strong enough. you’re powerful beyond measure. keep speaking your truth and trust me, your real “tribe” will find you. it’s so beautiful honestly. the real ones.
.
the past 20 months have been a wild ride for me. but standing in my truth and complete vulnerability with a deep resolve has healed me. you’ll always find it interesting who stands up, who sits down and who just puts on headphones to block out the noise when you talk about abuse and hard things. grab hands with the ones who stand up. they are your people🖤and remember the ones who betray us the most also showed us our power the most. my story is far from over and i’ve only started telling my truth. so to those men and women who took the side of my abuser, consider this my thank you...i never needed you to rise in power and continue to raise my voice. you can live in a delusional “reality” and i’ll walk in truth and live free. 🖤
.
📷: @najwazebian

text:
for you, jasper. for the month i lost you, march (aquamarine - blue), for your due date of october (secondary stone, sapphire - pink) and how your loss and due date happen to be the colors of miscarriage awareness. 
for you, jasper. for the way my #metoo echos in my soul for the rest of my life, for the shame, guilt, and tragedy i feel when i wake up and can sometimes feel them on me. 
for you, jasper. for how much i was terrified of you and your heartbeat, and how quickly broken i was when it was gone. 
for you, jasper. for why i’m still a politically pro choice, because being in a situation that breaks you in every way, a forced pregnancy shouldn’t be forced. even though my body chose for me. i would’ve figured it out for you, because myself i’m pro life. 
for you, jasper. for the ways sexual violence entered my life and the journey i’ve walked has been lonely, scary, silent. without god because i came to hate him and anyone who praised him, because how could god love us when life hurts us so bad? 
for you, jasper. for forcing me to learn faith again. to pray and learn, and try to find any god to comfort me. to make me look at myself as broken and shattered as i still am at times, and make me grow up. 
for you, jasper. for helping to learn love and learn of god and enjoy catholic mass. to helping me find people to pray with me, for me, and more importantly, for you. 
for you, jasper. for when fr. bob said you went straight to the loving arms of god and you knew nothing but of love. my love, you know no pain of them or of what they caused me. of the anguish your heartbeat caused me and the crushing defeat when it was gone. 
for you jasper. for making me advocate about rape, and sexual violence of male friends, and peers. advocating for mental health, eating disorders, suicide, self injury, sadness, anxiety, depression, and the devastation rape can cause. 
for you, jasper. you’re the closest lifeline i have to god, the closest thing i know how to get to god, because wherever you are, he is, and you my love, will stay in my heart. i’m ready to share our story, even if this is all i have to show for it. 
#metoo #mystory #myfaithjourney #irespectyou

text:
legacy: in the 90’s, after my mother passed away, my father applied for citizenship at the u.s. embassy in the philippines. he got the paperworks, filled them out, paid the fees and waited. he then flew to america first by himself, worked two to three jobs, slept in his car, sacrificed his health and saved enough money to buy plane tickets for all five of us children.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i pray i never take the opportunities i have here for granted. 🇺🇸 but even more so, to always be driven first and foremost by my god-given call and responsibility to give my children a better life, a better future —if only by doing my part in fighting for them today. just like my father did for us.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
despite the recent push for open and unlimited immigration, america does not owe the world free or automatic citizenship. it is a huge privilege that you earn, honor and respect. we are all dreamers, but in the end, there is a right way and a wrong way to go about turning those dreams into reality. #legalmakesthedifference ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
thank you @johnathon_miranda for nominating me. i nominate @jenmcanc @flipcs13 @spirit4me @vskylinespec @mcbrittsbaconbits and @zaythepatriot also, president trump will be at a rally today in el paso, tx! god bless america and cheers to legal, respectful and assimilating immigration!! 🇺🇸🙏🏼✊🏼💯

text:
la soirée «love-moi / like nous ! »
à suivre en 2019 ! 
déprimé(e), anxieux(se), perdu(e)?
(comme moi en 2016 : à lire +bas)
-êtes-vous à la croisée des chemins? -tanné(e) de chercher l’amour à travers l’opinion des autres ?
-épuisé(e) de rendre tout le monde heureux et manquer de temps pour vous mêmes? -avez-vous encore des buts et des rêves? ————————————————————-
en 2016 la dépression me frappe dur:

je réponds oui  à toutes ces questions ! 
j’atteins la noirceur, j’y resterai pendant des mois au point de vouloir en finir suite à une expérience #metoo avec une productrice d’hollywood qui me plonge dans une dépression majeure: je dois abandonné mon rêve sur lequel je travaille depuis 15 ans. je crois que ma valeur personnelle repose sur ce que je fais et ce que j’ai. je perds tous mes repères, incapable de sortir du lit, pu d’estime personnel. 
je vis des nuits d’insomnie infininies,de l’anxiété chronique, je suis à bout, un jour agenouillé en pleurs j’implore le bon dieu qu’il m’aide: « mon chum je fais un « deal » avec toi: je te promets que si je m’en sors vivant je veux que tu te sers de moi  pour inspirer les gens qui se sont perdus à retrouver la lumière en les aidant à reconnaitre leur valeur personnelle et talents. je veux les inspirer afin qu’ils vivent le bonheur d’une vie abondante . 
grâce à la présence d êtres chers, la persévérance, la foi et mes mentors le miracle prend forme: graduellement je reprends goût à la vie en comprenant que ma valeur personnelle se trouve dans l’être et non dans le faire ou l’avoir .
————————————————————-
en 2019 redonnons au suivant! ————————————————————-

text:
i just had a really deep soul session and a really good cry and then i got up and looked out to this sky.😭⁣
⁣
 it’s been dreary, dark and rainy all day...and now the sky is “on fire” at sunset. ⁣
⁣
this is a pretty good representation of my soul right now. i’m on freaking fire. ⁣
i’m so in love with digging deep and discovery the gifts and powers i possess that were buried under old trauma, self limiting beliefs, and fear most of my life. ⁣
⁣
thank you creator for always showing me what i need in every moment and more importantly showing me that slowing down and the silence is how i access the most beautiful parts of my soul. 🔥🔥🔥⁣

.

text:
⭐⭐⭐
the power - by naomi alderman
i wanted to love this ... i really (really did). touted by the likes of #time #obama and #margaretatwood  i bought the power in hard cover and couldn't even wait until my vacation to start reading. but, while alderman's writing was beautiful and the story was structured in such an interesting way, i was struck by how little i cared about what happened to the main characters. this was absolutely worth reading since it's a wonderful compliment to the #metoo movement and the strengths and limits of everything from contemporary #feminism to recorded #history but i was disappointed by the lack of connection i felt to the story and how familiar the arcs seemed (which admittedly may be a direct result of the issue laden hangover 2018 left me with).
recommended if you love:
#dystopian 
#feminist 
#fiction 
available in hard cover, paperback and on #audible

#yycreads #yycbooks #fiction
#feministliterature

text:
i've been challenged to remember why i do what i do. and not like to provide for my family. deeper than that. to recollect what made me start. what propels me? what will get me up each day. 
my 2. i don't want to just provide more for us. i want us to be able to dream so big and know that those dreams are attainable. i want to be a yes mom to my girl and give her more than just the necessities. her simple being propels me to be more and do more because i know she's watching. i know that when she repeats back to ke things that i have told her in situations that she is so aware. she is my biggest cheerleader and i know my life is a model to hers. i want her to see that if she has a heart for something she can make up her mind on it, work hard and attain it with god first. 
i want my husband to be able to do what pleases him in life and not have to put so much of the day to day struggle on his own back while putting himself in the rear. i know what that feels like and i know that he feels it. i want us both to live fulfilling lives and not just by money but in what we do and how we give. he has so many amazing ideas and he just needs the avenue. 
each day, i wake up knowing their dreams and have to know that if i attach my dreams to theirs, i have to get up and move. what do i dream of? i dream of the day when we are able to have the freedom of time for the moments like these to last just a little bit longer. when the hustle and bustle is not so poignant that it keeps us from relishing in the moments that we will never get back with our girl. 
i'm grateful that i have been given the opportunity with a business that can give me those things. sometimes the lord has a sense of humor because i chuckle and when i think about what this business has done for me. how much it kicks me out of my comfort zone and forces me to grow. how much that growth has made me realize the strength i have. how it helps me get through the month in between my monthly teacher salary. the thrill i get to experience when my customers are excited about how the product works for them. 
what is your why? what do you do it for? are you in need of more? let's talk about it! #metoo #wifemomboss

text:
today marks 14 years since a masked man jumped & sexually assaulted me at gunpoint.

that’s 5,110 days of fear, overthinking, over analyzing every situation. getting up in the middle of the night to make sure the front door is locked, flinching every time i hear footsteps behind me, flashbacks every time i see a ski mask.

since that day though i’ve been aware of god’s presence in my life more than ever. i’ve been aware of my guardian angels more than ever. if my anxiety acts up - a quick word of prayer releases any doubt or fear filling up in my body. 
last year was the first time i openly shared my story and i do plan to continuously share it because for a long time i was ashamed or blamed myself and it’s unfair for a teenaged girl (or any age) to think that she did anything to fuel toxic masculinity in any form. so many women in our caribbean community reached out to me after i shared the first time thanking me for telling my truth and i appreciate every single one of you. “she was powerful, not because she wasn’t scared but because she went on so strongly despite the fear” -atticus ✨

#metoo

since that day though i’ve been aware of god’s presence in my life more than ever. i’ve been aware of my guardian angels more than ever. if my anxiety acts up - a quick word of prayer releases any doubt or fear filling up in my body. 
last year was the first time i openly shared my story and i do plan to continuously share it because for a long time i was ashamed or blamed myself and it’s unfair for a teenaged girl (or any age) to think that she did anything to fuel toxic masculinity in any form. so many women in our caribbean community reached out to me after i shared the first time thanking me for telling my truth and i appreciate every single one of you. “she was powerful, not because she wasn’t scared but because she went on so strongly despite the fear” -atticus ✨

text:
u.s. news

more than 200 baptist ministers, deacons and others have been found guilty of sex abuse, report says

a total of about 380 southern baptist leaders and volunteers have faced allegations of sexual misconduct, a newspaper investigation found.

people pray during the annual meeting of the southern baptist convention on june 14, 2016, in st. louis.jeff roberson / ap file

for more than a decade, a baptist preacher in oklahoma has been what he calls "a lone voice in the wilderness."
pastor wade burleson called on the southern baptist convention to protect its flock by creating a database that would track church workers accused of sexual abuse.

such a list was published monday, but not by the baptists.

the houston chronicle and san antonio express-news in an expansive investigation named 220 #pastors, #ministers, #deacons, #volunteers, #sundayschool #teachers and others who were found guilty of sexually abusing #churchgoers over 20 years.
more than 250 have been charged. and roughly 380 southern baptist church leaders and volunteers have faced allegations of sexual misconduct involving more than 700 victims, the report found. that includes those who were convicted, credibly accused and successfully sued.
some of the victims were molested repeatedly and some were as young as 3, according to the report.

related

#metoo goes to church: southern baptists face a reckoning over treatment of women

the news outlets' yearlong investigation also found that three dozen pastors and workers who have been suspected of being predators continue to work for baptist churches. “the thing that makes me saddest is that we didn’t do it ourselves,” burleson told nbc news of the report. “that’s why you need a free press in america.”
calling the report a “punch in the gut,” burleson predicted it will lead to real change in the way the southern baptist convention, the largest protestant organization in the country, grapples with an issue that has also forced a reckoning in the roman catholic church and the orthodox jewish community.
“the analogy i would give is this: i recently had a cancerous lesion removed from my skin

text:
자신에게 존댓말을 사용하지 않았다는 이유로 화를 내는 한국 남성들이 참 놀랍다. 그 화를 한국 사회가 여성을 대하는 방식에 대해 표출하면 참 좋을 것을.

한국에서는 문장 끝에 “요”를 붙이지 않으면 무례하다고 지적하지만, 여성과 남성의 40% 임금 격차나 직장에서 계속되는 성희롱의 무례함에 대해서는 한 마디도 하지 않는다.

말 끝에 “요”를 붙이며 가식적으로 사람들을 존중하는 ‘척’하는 사회 보다 차라리 존댓말 없이 서로를 ‘진정으로’ 동등하게 대하는 사회에서 살고 싶다.

it's amazing how offended some korean men get when you don't use proper honorifics. imagine if they got that angry over the way women are treated in korea..
.
forget to add a "요" at the end of a sentence and they find you disrespectful, but hardly a word about the 40% pay gap in korea or the constant sexual harassment at work.

i'd much rather live in a society where we didn't use honorifics but we treated everyone equally, rather than pretend we respect each other because we add a "요"  at the end of every sentence.

#koreanfeminist #metoo  #페미니즘 #페미니스트 #feminism #feminist

text:
i promise to:

dedicate as much energy & time
as is humanly possible, to become aware of my own self worth, development of my potential, praising & pleasing myself, and following my intuition, as i have encouraged others to do over the years.

i discovered that i only felt valuable to others if i was giving them something or doing something for someone. i did not hold a space of being valuable simply for being me. i believed that, only if i had some tangible action or gift to give away, would i be liked or loved. **this belief is no longer my truth.

so when i suffered from physical, mental, and emotional exhaustion and even depleted my savings, i looked around to others that i have tried to be supportive of and did not have the same reciprocity.
i have actually been shamed for reaching out for help.
which showed me that, i must go deeper inward to learn to sustain, nourish, teach and heal myself. 
i am the one i have needed to come forth for all of these years. i am the one who needs to value my own presence. i am the one who needs to respect my boundaries. 
i am the one who needs to cherish my happiness, well-being, wealth of knowledge, and advice.
i am the one that needs to pursue her goals with the same, if not more, amount of enthusiasm as i have encouraged others in my life to do.
i am silently achieving accomplishments off of my list. not to prove to anyone else but myself, that it can be done.  as long as i am in alignment with my purpose, my every step brings me closer to making my creative imagination into a tangible experience, that many can benefit from.
it is truly amazing when you can recognize that setbacks are often actually setups to achieve a new level of strength!!! before i go i'm just wondering something. if you knew it was time to journey across a new unfamiliar terrain, would you rather have a guide that read a book about the terrain or a guide that has actually made the trek several dozen times mastered the best routes, pathways, shortcuts, and tools you would need along that journey?

#mondaymotivation
#promisekeeper #yourlife #yourchoice

text:
tarana burke was born september 12, 1973 in the bronx, ny. she is an african-american civil rights activist. she's most well-known as the founder of the "me too" movement in 2006 after a thirteen year old girl revealed that her mother’s boyfriend had been sexually abusing her. 
burke was left searching for the right words to help empathize with the countless women and young girls who have disclosed their experiences to her. 
the movement has blossomed into a worldwide campaign to raise awareness about sexual harassment, abuse, and assault in society. in 2017, burke and other influential female activists were named "the silence breakers" by time magazine. she currently serves at the girls for gender equity in brooklyn as its senior director and has used the power of her idea to speak at events and encourage healing for others.

#blackhistorymonth #day11 #taranaburke #metoo #empathy #silencebreakers #knowyourhistory #ourlegacy

text:
🌸ひな祭りdeけんぽうカフェ🌸
1月大好評だったため、引き続き2月も
金・土曜開催決定‼️ 2/16と2/22よー

2月も、ゆるゆると
初心者による初心者のための、
けんぽうカフェ開催いたしま〜す☺️
今月の先取りタイトルは『ひな祭り』よ💖
憲法カフェも開始してから1年経過し
今月も２回開催しますっっっ！

私達が使うわかりやすい言葉で、
生活に結びついてる憲法を楽しく学びましょう。
毎回テーマを決めてます。
2月のテーマは
『96条 憲法改正』
どうやって憲法改正していくの？国民投票って？？
まず、知りましょう😊

今、話題のニュースは憲法とどう繋がっているのか
大好評の憲法ビンゴなどで楽しく学んでいきます。
コーヒーやお菓子つまみつつ
 一緒に楽しい時間を過ごしましょう！
いつ来ても、帰ってもokです♪ 💝  #ひな祭りdeけんぽうカフェ💝
日時: 2/16土曜 pm13時から15時  2/22金曜am10時から12時
場所 : 浦和パルコ9階コムナーレ　浦和駅東口徒歩1分（さいたま市民活動サポートセンター）奥の飲食可のスペースでやってます。
費用: 100円 ( 飲み物、資料代込み)
メンバーが、持ち寄って
お菓子コーヒー用意してお待ちしてまーす♪

text:
i often get asked about why i got this tattoo. i usually say “i just like palm trees idk”.
i got this tattoo october 28, 2018. 2 months prior to walking into the shop, i was actually walking into a hospital with the police, where i endured a 7 hour rape kit, 18 std prevention pills, emergency hiv/aids meds, and a follow-up to reassess the internal injuries i sustained. my clothes were thrown into a brown paper bag and the police told me that i would most likely never get them back.
i have suffered from ptsd, anxiety, and depression every single day since then, but somehow i made it into that tattoo shop to get a palm tree done, the branch of which is a symbol of victory & triumph.
since that day, i began to redefine what triumph & victory are in my life. i no longer prided myself on things most would deem commendable. my new victory was getting out of bed in the morning but i forced my social media to make it seem as if i was doing more. after a few months,  i managed to actually do more, and began to reclaim part of myself.
5 days before christmas, the da informed me she did not intend to prosecute my case.
for a long time after that, i no longer saw the point in the little victories if there was no longer an attainable justice to serve as my big victory.
the hype of #metoo has died down & the women’s march is over but i still exist outside of those movements. i’m still here when the hashtags disappear & the signs get put up in the attic & the news cycle forgets my statistics. so now what?
i’m leaving this post open-ended because that’s what it’s like to be a sexual assault survivor. there is no magic formula or set timeline for recovery. sometimes it feels like the world has kept moving while i’ve been standing perfectly still. i feel at war with myself as i grapple to make sense of how i can be put together one day & sobbing on the floor the next.
but at the end of it all, i am still victorious & triumphant because i am still alive & that’s enough. i am not ashamed of who i am and this palm tree reminds me that even on my worst day, there are still moments to take pride in.
let’s go forth with pride and love for ourselves today.

but at the end of it all, i am still victorious & triumphant because i am still alive & that’s enough. i am not ashamed of who i am and this palm tree reminds me that even on my worst day, there are still moments to take pride in.
let’s go forth with pride and love for ourselves today.

i got this tattoo october 28, 2018. 2 months prior to walking into the shop, i was actually walking into a hospital with the police, where i endured a 7 hour rape kit, 18 std prevention pills, emergency hiv/aids meds, and a follow-up to reassess the internal injuries i sustained. my clothes were thrown into a brown paper bag and the police told me that i would most likely never get them back.
i have suffered from ptsd, anxiety, and depression every single day since then, but somehow i made it into that tattoo shop to get a palm tree done, the branch of which is a symbol of victory & triumph.
since that day, i began to redefine what triumph & victory are in my life. i no longer prided myself on things most would deem commendable. my new victory was getting out of bed in the morning but i forced my social media to make it seem as if i was doing more. after a few months,  i managed to actually do more, and began to reclaim pa of myself.
5 days before christmas, the da informed me she did not intend to prosecute my case.
for a long time after that, i no longer saw the point in the little victories if there was no longer an attainable justice to serve as my big victory.

text:
women inmates would be guaranteed access to hygiene products under legislation that was ok’d in its first committee monday.

the measure (sb 332), filed by sen. jason pizzo and reviewed by the senate criminal justice committee, was approved unanimously.

it’s the counterpart to legislation (hb 49) filed by state reps. shevrin jones and amy mercado in the house.

the legislation, dubbed the “dignity for incarcerated women act,” was filed in response to reports regarding the treatment of women inmates, particularly in light of the #metoo movement.

pizzo’s measure ensures access to feminine hygiene products, as well as toothbrushes, soap and other items at no cost to the inmates.

the long anticipated 'bad mothers' is premiering on @channel9 monday 18 february at 9pm. we're looking forward to watching this female-led show, with a fantastic cast including @shalombf
.

"arriving in an era of #metoo bad mothers also maintains plenty of women behind the scenes. 'two directors are female. it is a very female crew. there are a lot of women in the camera and art departments, sound dept, continuity. having a balance of genders really changes the dynamic of a set. you can tell the energy is different,' says tovey. 'there are lots of components to #metoo. it’s not just about sexual harassment in the industry. that’s at the core of it but it speaks more largely to women finding their voice, and that’s something we should talk a lot more about.'
